Usage: define_parameter [-help] [<setup/hold>] [-correlation <string>]
                        [-distribution <string>] [-moments <string>]
                        [-name <string>] [-range <string>] [-related <string>]
                        -scope <string> [-view <string>]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
<setup/hold>               # parameter is valid for setup hold ( setup|hold )
                           # (string, optional)
-correlation <string>      # correlation between different parameters of same
                           # scope. parameters need to be predefined
                           # (string, optional)
-distribution <string>     # parameter distribution. Can also use custom
                           # distribution pre-defined (string, optional)
-moments <string>          # Parameter moments {mean std-dev}
                           # (string, optional)
-name <string>             # parameter name (string, optional)
-range <string>            # Parameter min/max range {min max}.
                           # (string, optional)
-related <string>          # Specifies related information on sub-scope of
                           # parameter within specified -scope.For BEOL, the
                           # allowed arguments are: 1. <layer name>:capacitance
                           # 2. <layer name>:resistance (string, optional)
-scope <string>            # parameter scope (
                           # vtskew|wire_variation|via_variation )
                           # (string, required)
-view <string>             # View name (string, optional)